.TH DBX-QUERY 1 "2026-06-20" "dbx 0.36.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dbx-query \- open an interactive shell against a database
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dbx query
.I host
.RI [ database ]
.PP
.B dbx q
.I host
.RI [ database ]
.PP
.B dbx shell
.I host
.RI [ database ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Open
.B psql
(Postgres) or
.B mysql
(MySQL / MariaDB) against the named host. Uses the same SSH-tunneled
container infrastructure as
.B dbx backup ,
so no local DB client is needed.
.PP
If
.I host
has
.BR safety=prod
in
.IR config.json ,
the session is opened in READ ONLY mode: writes are refused server-side
via
.IR default_transaction_read_only=on
(Postgres) or
.IR --skip-secure-auth
+ session-level read-only (MySQL).
.SH EXAMPLES
Open psql against
.IR production / myapp :
.PP
.RS
.nf
dbx query production myapp
.fi
.RE
.SH SAFETY
Per-host
.IR safety
flag in
.IR config.json :
.TP
.B prod
Session opens READ ONLY. Writes are refused at the server.
.TP
.B stage " or " local
No restriction; session is read/write.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dbx (1),
.BR dbx-test (1),
.BR dbx-config (1).
